

谓语
	Predicate (谓语) 在日语中通常称为 述語 (じゅつご - jutsu-go)
	谓语（Predicate）就是一句话中表示主语的 动作 或 	状态 的部分，通常是句子里唯一真正变形的动词（根据时态、人称、单复数而变化）。
	谓语 = 句子的“动词引擎”
	
	没有谓语，句子不完整。
	❌ The weather in Tokyo yesterday.
	✔ The weather in Tokyo was great yesterday.
	（“was” = 谓语 → 才变成完整句）

非谓语动词 非述語動詞(準動詞) — 「不定詞・分詞・動名詞」
	to do（不定式）
	doing（动名词/现在分词）
	done（过去分词）	
	Running every day is good for your health.
	running = 非谓语（修饰，不能当句子动作）



一般表达（5.5）	非谓语表达（7.0+）
	People who live in cities have more job opportunities.	

	People living in cities have more job opportunities.

	When technology develops, society changes.	

	With technology developing, society changes
	With cities expanding rapidly, housing prices have soared.


[]With + 名词 + 现在分词 → 表示背景/原因，更 concise。
	With globalisation accelerating, people work across borders.

[]Despite 
	Although she studied hard, she failed the exam.
	Despite studying hard, she failed the exam.
[]Driven by 
	Driven by increasing competition, companies are adopting automation
	Driven by globalisation, people work across borders.
[]Fueled by 
	Fueled by rapid urbanisation, housing prices have soared.
[]Triggered by / Amid / As a result of / In response to
[]In light of 鉴于
	In light of the growing popularity of online education, it is essential to evaluate its impact on traditional schools.
	In light of recent environmental concerns, governments must prioritise renewable energy.
	In light of increasing life expectancy, many countries face pension challenges.
	In light of recent economic downturns, many families are cutting expenses.


---
名词化
	expansion
	- The expansion of urban areas causes environmental strain.